## Events Count Evolution
A graph showing how many events happened over time.

Think of it like a heartbeat monitor:
```
Many events  → System is active
Zero events  → Quiet OR agent stopped sending
Sudden spike → Something unusual happened — investigate
```

In SOC work — a sudden spike in events at 3am = investigate immediately.

---

## MITRE ATT&CK
A global database of real attacker techniques used in real attacks.

Wazuh maps suspicious behaviors to known attack techniques automatically.

Example:
```
Someone runs a hidden PowerShell command
        ↓
Wazuh detects it
        ↓
Maps it to MITRE technique: Defense Evasion
        ↓
Alert created
```

Every technique has a T-number code:

| Code | Technique | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| T1078 | Valid Accounts | Using legitimate credentials |
| T1562.001 | Disable Security Tools | Turning off antivirus or security |
| T1059 | Command Line Interface | Running commands via terminal |
| T1055 | Process Injection | Hiding malware inside legitimate process |

