## SYSTEM Account — Important To Understand

SYSTEM = Windows internal account used by the OS itself.

Normal SYSTEM behavior:
- Starting Windows services (Logon Type 5)
- Running system processes like services.exe
- Managing internal Windows operations

Suspicious SYSTEM behavior:
| Behavior | Why Suspicious |
|---|---|
| Making outbound network connections | SYSTEM never initiates external connections |
| Creating files in unusual locations | Possible malware |
| Running PowerShell | Possible attack |
| Logon from external IP | Impossible normally — definite attack |

