## SOC Analyst Daily Workflow With SIEM

```
Start shift
        ↓
Open SIEM dashboard
        ↓
Sort alerts by severity — Critical first
        ↓
Investigate Critical and High alerts
        ↓
Apply O-M-C to each alert
        ↓
True Positive → Escalate to senior analyst
False Positive → Document and close
        ↓
Move to Medium and Low alerts
        ↓
End of shift report
```

---

## The Golden Rule of SIEM Investigation

> 80% of alerts are false positives.
> Your job is to find the real 20%.

The skill is not just detecting threats — it is correctly identifying what is normal and what is not.

---

## Common Mistakes

- ❌ Investigating all alerts equally — always prioritize by severity
- ❌ Closing alerts without documentation
- ❌ Assuming SYSTEM account activity is always normal
- ❌ Missing the one unusual event in a sea of normal events
- ❌ Not checking the process name behind an alert
- ❌ Confusing False Positive with False Negative

